  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180C.",
    "Rinse and slice peppadew peppers into thin strips.",
    "In a large bowl, combine sliced peppers, diced bamboo shoots, rolled oats, chickpea flour, cumin, smoked paprika, cayenne, and sea salt.",
    "Drizzle olive oil and lemon juice over mixture and toss until everything is evenly coated.",
    "Transfer the pepper mixture to a greased baking dish and spread it out in an even layer.",
    "Sprinkle chopped parsley on top of the peppers.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 12 minutes, or until the crumble edges are golden and the mixture is heated through.",
    "Remove from oven, let cool for a minute, then serve warm as a romantic side or topping."
